Redesign UI as a platform + expand agent marketplace

Frontend
- New pastel-green design system (pastel-green canvas, white surfaces,
  dark-green primary, tan accents); smaller type scale; far fewer boxes.
- Drop the oversized "Private Banker for the 99%" hero, mission strip, fake
  scripted progress steps, mic button, and the always-$0 Family Payment bucket.
- Remove the "Demo only" badge; keep a "Testnet USDC" pill.
- Two-column platform layout (chat/automations/agents + portfolio/activity).

Functionality
- Automations tab: manual create form (recurring transfer / protect funds),
  posting to the existing POST /api/automations.
- Agent marketplace: live roster fetched from /api/marketplace with online
  status, risk band, representative APY, and unlock state by risk + balance.
- Create agents on the fly: POST /api/marketplace turns a plain-English goal
  into a structured strategy spec via Claude (lib/agent-factory), persisted in
  the registry and served by the shared local strategy engine (~4-5s, one call).
- Expand the roster to 6 risk-tiered agents (Savings, Stable-Invest,
  Balanced-Growth, Growth [min $500], High-Yield [min $1000], Bill-Pay) with
  new uAgents (ports 8004-8006) + strategies; auto-selection gates by risk AND
  amount, stepping down when the balance can't unlock a tier.

Portfolio buckets simplified to Available / Protected / Invested; all investing
agents pool into the Invested bucket so the marketplace can grow without adding
buckets. Verified live: build + lint green, demo + recovery prompts, high-risk
routing to High-Yield, manual automation, and dynamic agent creation.

